108. Boia is a pun, meaning both a Boian woman, and a kind of collar worn by slaves. Erg. says Stal. must be a Boian, because he is wedded to a “ Boia.'' The Boii were a powerful and warlike people of Upper Italy, who had on several occasions caused the· Romans much annoyance, especially in the Second Punic War; their complete subjection by Scipio Nasica and incorporation in the province of Gallia Cisalpina (13.6. 191) was an event still fresh in the memory of the audience.
